with every girl you met?

12:07.178 --> 12:10.262
It was for a Green Card
to keep me working there.

12:10.362 --> 12:13.970
- You were going to pay to marry her?
- Why the hell would I do that?

12:14.070 --> 12:16.603
Jesus Christ! Your English is shit!
Be fucking clearer?

12:16.703 --> 12:19.987
We wanted to keep things going between us,
you know. See if we had something.

12:20.087 --> 12:23.078
- The Green Card was her idea.
- And you fucked it up?

12:23.478 --> 12:24.820
Why do you think it was me
that fucked it up?

12:24.920 --> 12:27.807
It's 50/50.
More than likely, it's you, no?

12:27.907 --> 12:34.138
We were both twenty. Okay? Very twenty.

12:34.820 --> 12:37.053
- What does it matter now anyway?
- Maybe this is a second chance.

12:37.153 --> 12:39.503
It could be fate.

12:40.070 --> 12:44.012
- You always say you don't believe in fate.
- Yes, because I have thought about it a lot.

12:44.112 --> 12:46.820
You? You could definitely
believe in this bullshit.

12:47.620 --> 12:50.462
Look, it's not like I haven't been able
to stop thinking about her all these years.

12:50.562 --> 12:54.995
I have. I just haven't been able
to forget her either.

12:55.095 --> 12:58.420
And she is somewhere
out there right now.

12:59.820 --> 13:02.796
I didn't exactly leave things
on the best of terms back in the day.

13:02.896 --> 13:05.540
You should've brought her to your place.
Who know what happens?

13:05.740 --> 13:07.503
She's probably got a boyfriend anyway.

13:07.803 --> 13:10.998
- You're so stuck in your pants!
- I'm not stuck in my pants.

13:11.098 --> 13:15.767
Every day you're closer to dying alone with
nothing but a blanket of shit around you.

13:15.867 --> 13:17.603
- A blanket of...
- A blanket of shit, Alan!

13:17.703 --> 13:21.720
That's great. Lovely thing to say to me.

13:53.503 --> 13:55.662
- How's the head?
- Grand.

13:57.053 --> 13:59.537
<i>Hola</i>, Beatrice.

13:59.937 --> 14:03.344
I was thinking about our gig last night.
Maybe we need a new band photo.

14:04.037 --> 14:05.562
What's wrong with the one we have?

14:05.962 --> 14:09.512
Well, I just think we've moved on
from our hillbilly goth phase.

14:09.612 --> 14:12.929
True. Talking of changes...

14:13.029 --> 14:15.145
maybe it's time we started
playing weddings.

14:16.845 --> 14:19.782
You want our band to play Sting, is that
what you want? Fields of fuckin' Gold!

14:19.882 --> 14:22.028
Come on, man, it's been over a year now.

14:22.128 --> 14:25.853
It's not about that. If we go down that road,
there's no more real gigs left.

14:25.953 --> 14:27.712
And you know that, right?
Is that what you want?

14:27.812 --> 14:30.262
We could all do
with a bit of extra dough.

14:30.362 --> 14:32.862
I've been trying to finish the jacks
in me gaff for the last 12 months.

14:32.962 --> 14:34.116
I don't mind,

14:34.216 --> 14:37.137
but Deirdre's getting tired of the
neighbours watching her do her business.

14:37.237 --> 14:41.203
My sister's got us an easy gig.
It's a grand each.

14:41.303 --> 14:44.320
- I'm not playing weddings.
- I can't hear a word you're saying, man!

14:44.420 --> 14:47.507
- Look, you think about it, yeah?
- I'm not...

14:47.607 --> 14:49.902
I'm not playing...

15:24.678 --> 15:26.950
Thanks very much. Bye.

15:30.503 --> 15:32.762
- Hey!
- Hi!

15:33.462 --> 15:35.614
What are you doin' here?

15:37.278 --> 15:41.619
Well, I just couldn't get
that Post-it out of my mind.

15:43.403 --> 15:46.553
Plus it looks like I might get out of here
tonight which would be amazing.

15:46.653 --> 15:49.820
Cool. Well, that's a shame.

15:50.120 --> 15:53.487
I could've shown you around town
a bit if you were staying longer.

15:53.587 --> 15:55.595
- Guess it wasn't meant to be.
- Yeah.

15:56.095 --> 16:02.289
I mean, I don't suppose...
if you want... maybe stay?

16:04.520 --> 16:06.990
What's an evening?
Get a flight tomorrow.

16:07.090 --> 16:10.311
Well, that's a little presumptuous.
I mean...

16:10.411 --> 16:12.837
how do you know
I don't have responsibilities?

16:13.237 --> 16:14.312
Oh, do you?

16:15.412 --> 16:16.695
Nothing comes to mind.

16:16.795 --> 16:19.662
I think I owe you a night out.
No funny business, I promise.

16:19.762 --> 16:22.570
- Then I'm definitely going home.
- Hi, can I help you?

16:22.870 --> 16:25.025
Hi. I'm on standby
for a flight to New York.

16:25.125 --> 16:26.866
I was told I might be able
to get out tonight.

16:26.966 --> 16:29.226
Okay, I'll check for you now.

16:29.696 --> 16:32.869
No, sorry, best we can do
is tomorrow morning.

16:37.820 --> 16:41.078
If you had a summer romance
with someone eight years ago

16:41.178 --> 16:44.968
and they wanted you to stay
an extra night to catch up,

16:45.278 --> 16:47.354
would you do it?

16:47.720 --> 16:50.214
- And no funny business?
- No.

16:50.520 --> 16:51.624
Like nothing?

16:52.970 --> 16:54.221
Well, I can.

16:55.137 --> 16:58.052
- Can he?
- A while ago, maybe.

16:59.737 --> 17:03.803
- Yeah. Life's short. Why not?
- Thanks.

17:03.903 --> 17:06.853
Sure there's no other flights?
I'm kidding.

17:07.453 --> 17:12.021
Or if you slip me 10 euro, I can
get you on a first class seat tonight.

17:12.744 --> 17:15.459
- What?
- I'm kidding also.

17:19.470 --> 17:21.720
Alright.

17:22.362 --> 17:23.288
Bye.

17:26.737 --> 17:31.262
Just so you know, I live with my dad.
I know it's not a big deal, but...

17:31.362 --> 17:33.745
Who doesn't live
with their folks these days?

17:33.845 --> 17:38.188
- You do?
- No! No!

17:40.112 --> 17:43.237
I didn't... I didn't mean...
That sounded like I...

17:43.337 --> 17:45.220
- Fine. It's fine.
- I just...

17:45.320 --> 17:48.083
A lot of my friends ended up in houses
they couldn't pay for and...

17:48.183 --> 17:50.770
- had to move back home.
- Right.

17:50.870 --> 17:53.512
It's just... It's super common,
that's what I'm saying.

17:53.612 --> 17:56.884
You're right. It's all around, you know.

18:00.420 --> 18:04.086
Well, this... definitely...

18:04.186 --> 18:06.491
a temporary thing.

18:07.903 --> 18:09.370
The...

18:09.470 --> 18:12.728
- Living with my dad.
- Oh, right!

18:19.870 --> 18:22.062
- Call it.
- You just say, 'Call'.

18:22.162 --> 18:24.237
- Then call me.
- You want me to ring ya?

18:25.137 --> 18:27.520
You know what I mean!

18:28.562 --> 18:29.787
Here's the man with the plan.

18:29.887 --> 18:31.595
- Alright, Alan?
- Howya, lads.

18:32.095 --> 18:34.418
That's not all he's got.

18:34.518 --> 18:37.382
- This is Alice.
- Hey, guys!

18:39.453 --> 18:40.887
It's alright. She's American.

18:41.589 --> 18:42.891
Okay.

18:43.695 --> 18:46.503
Okay, well, I'll just show you
to your quarters.

18:46.803 --> 18:48.695
There's beers in the fridge
if you want them.

18:48.795 --> 18:52.038
- Okay, great.
- Won't be there for long though!

18:54.012 --> 18:55.728
Fiver says he blows it.

18:58.562 --> 19:02.912
- Some kind of poker night out there?
- Divorced men's support group.

19:03.870 --> 19:05.608
They mainly play poker.

19:11.070 --> 19:14.392
- I'll sleep on the couch.
- Okay.

19:15.828 --> 19:18.072
Great.

19:20.703 --> 19:24.125
No way! You still play barefoot?

19:24.395 --> 19:26.412
I never play barefoot.

19:26.912 --> 19:31.439
I remember your whole sensitive
musician schtick you had going on.

19:34.070 --> 19:37.912
I bet there's not a single Depeche Mode
track among all these records.

19:38.012 --> 19:41.777
If you're gonna love a band, it has to be
based around more than one or two singles.

19:41.877 --> 19:44.006
One or two?

19:48.970 --> 19:53.055
- So it's been...
- Eight years.

19:54.345 --> 19:56.298
Our twenties.

19:56.398 --> 19:59.282
Yeah. How was it for you?

20:00.695 --> 20:03.012
I was on high terror alert
for most of it.

20:03.112 --> 20:06.731
Mainly because some of my friends decided
they had to have babies, like, right know,

20:06.831 --> 20:09.210
- which freaked me out.
- Right.

20:11.612 --> 20:13.831
What about you?

20:14.362 --> 20:18.645
No babies, but it's definitely
had its moments.

20:21.012 --> 20:23.678
Oh, is there somewhere
I could charge this? I just...

20:23.778 --> 20:26.837
I'm supposed to hear about the job.
I don't want to miss the call.

20:26.937 --> 20:29.179
Yeah, sure.

20:31.920 --> 20:35.295
That's the main character.
His name is Victor.

20:35.395 --> 20:38.197
The writer's this French guy, and they
want somebody to illustrate the books.

20:38.297 --> 20:42.337
I'm one of the last two up for the gig.
Could be a big break, finally.

20:42.437 --> 20:44.120
So, what's the story with Victor?

20:44.220 --> 20:47.525
He's one of these kids
that reads everything.

20:47.625 --> 20:51.402
So this mysterious mobile library
comes to his town

20:51.502 --> 20:55.120
and they tell him there's one book left
that he hasn't read,

20:55.220 --> 20:57.353
but that he's not allowed.

20:57.453 --> 21:02.647
So he steals the book and it turns out
that it's a biography of his own life

21:02.747 --> 21:08.020
from the future where he's basically
the most hated man in the world.

21:08.120 --> 21:10.195
That's a bit rough.

21:10.295 --> 21:14.420
And so he's got to try and avoid
this destiny and shape a new one, but...

21:14.926 --> 21:17.772
it turns out it's easier said than done.

21:18.962 --> 21:21.737
That's him fighting the forces of fate.

21:21.837 --> 21:24.195
There's also a seagull named Charles,
who helps him out.

21:24.295 --> 21:27.879
It's basically Harry Potter
but with wine bars.

21:28.279 --> 21:29.970
So what happens in the end?

21:30.874 --> 21:33.224
Not for another ten books.

21:34.178 --> 21:38.092
This is just showing what else I can do.

21:39.420 --> 21:42.001
Life drawings.

21:43.020 --> 21:44.425
This is my apartment.

21:45.953 --> 21:48.095
He just happened to be there?

21:48.780 --> 21:50.970
That's Brian. We're seeing each other.

21:51.070 --> 21:54.243
- He's a lawyer.
- Clearly.

21:54.953 --> 21:56.828
He's actually quite shy.

21:56.928 --> 21:59.920
Oh, right. Not the talkative,
naked lawyer type?

22:02.420 --> 22:04.612
Well, you seem to have it all
figured out, Alice.

22:11.237 --> 22:12.594
You have a girlfriend?

22:16.643 --> 22:18.583
Yeah.

22:19.287 --> 22:21.845
Good for you. What's she like?

22:21.945 --> 22:25.088
Good, grand.

22:25.920 --> 22:29.662
I could draw you some detailed
matchstick figures of her if you like.

22:29.762 --> 22:32.305
That's alright. Wait a second.

22:32.405 --> 22:37.137
You guys don't have some romantic evening
planned? I don't want to crash anything.

22:37.453 --> 22:39.820
No, we don't really celebrate
Valentine's Day.

22:40.820 --> 22:42.826
But you give each other cards?

22:43.023 --> 22:47.035
Yeah. That's just a bit of fun.

22:47.678 --> 22:50.362
- Maybe this was a bad idea.
- No.

22:50.462 --> 22:54.853
No, no, no, no, it's cool. I will give her
a call to see if she's around.

22:54.953 --> 22:57.545
And... you know, we can hook up.

22:57.645 --> 23:00.572
- You're sure?
- Absolutely, yeah.

23:01.445 --> 23:05.212
Okay. I'll just...
I guess I'll just change.

23:05.312 --> 23:07.593
Okay, grand.

23:08.745 --> 23:10.937
Hey, Alan.

23:12.525 --> 23:14.378
It's really good to see you again.

23:15.378 --> 23:17.581
Yeah, you too.

23:21.870 --> 23:24.209
I panicked. Alright?

23:25.312 --> 23:28.295
No, no, no, this is what happens
when I put myself in this kind of situation.

23:29.095 --> 23:31.335
I need your help.

23:32.912 --> 23:37.750
Forty Euros, a meal
and a taxi fare home.

23:37.870 --> 23:41.507
And all the cigarettes
that you can smoke.

23:43.204 --> 23:45.595
Thanks. Thank you.

23:50.478 --> 23:53.218
- Here, moneybags!
- What do you want?

23:53.678 --> 23:56.075
Change in fifties.

23:56.175 --> 23:58.887
Here, grab us one of mine, will ya?

23:58.987 --> 24:01.251
Yep.

24:01.778 --> 24:03.007
Who's the bird?

24:04.520 --> 24:06.828
They can't keep their hands
off me, you know.

24:06.928 --> 24:08.612
- Since when?
- Since forever.

24:09.412 --> 24:10.953
Who is she?

24:11.053 --> 24:13.878
We worked together a few
summers ago in Martha's Vineyard.

24:13.978 --> 24:15.951
She's only here for a couple of hours.
Her flight's in the morning.

24:16.051 --> 24:18.130
All part of the service now, is it?

24:22.320 --> 24:25.757
- Beers in the fridge.
- Oh, thanks, cool.

24:31.695 --> 24:33.663
Would you fuckin' stop!

24:35.462 --> 24:37.320
Alright?

24:38.737 --> 24:41.062
So Alan tells me you guys
get together and stuff?

24:41.462 --> 24:43.912
All you have to do is get married
and divorced to join us, Alice.

24:44.212 --> 24:45.553
Is that all?

24:45.653 --> 24:47.587
I'm gonna change out of these things.
I'll just be a sec.

24:47.687 --> 24:50.603
Okay. Got room for another?

24:50.703 --> 24:54.945
- Sure. But we only play for real money.
- That's a shame. I only have Euros.

24:58.037 --> 25:00.628
A euro and you're in.

25:03.153 --> 25:05.086
Do you guys ever think
about getting remarried?

25:05.402 --> 25:06.394
No!

25:07.370 --> 25:09.250
We've had enough of lies, Alice.

25:10.153 --> 25:15.078
I'm sure men lie just as much
as women do. That's my opinion.

25:15.178 --> 25:16.603
Check.

25:16.703 --> 25:18.420
Check.

25:18.520 --> 25:20.409
Raise.

25:22.184 --> 25:24.887
- I'm out.
- I'm gonna stay for five.

25:26.682 --> 25:27.978
I'll go along.

25:28.278 --> 25:32.162
In my experience, Alice,
men lie because they have to.

25:32.262 --> 25:33.837
Women lie because they can.

25:33.937 --> 25:36.753
A guy once lied to me
and told me his mother was dying

25:36.853 --> 25:39.062
just so he could put his hand up
my sweater. I mean...

25:39.162 --> 25:42.445
that's pretty messed up, but I'm sure
you guys can all beat that, right?

25:43.245 --> 25:45.595
My wife handpicked
our wedding photographer.

25:45.695 --> 25:48.020
She said he was the best, and he was.

25:48.320 --> 25:49.920
Because when he sent me
the wrong photographs,

25:50.020 --> 25:52.570
I could see that they were
handpicking each other.

25:52.670 --> 25:55.595
- It's true.
- Raise you five.

25:57.195 --> 25:59.220
I'm out.

25:59.320 --> 26:02.370
This girl I once knew, her boyfriend
secretly filmed them having sex.

26:02.470 --> 26:06.796
And then, when they broke up,
he accidentally but yet anonymously

26:06.896 --> 26:08.720
sent it to everybody
that she works with.

26:08.820 --> 26:11.770
That being a sixth grade class
that she teaches.

26:14.770 --> 26:16.845
All in.

26:19.537 --> 26:22.604
Well, I'll... call.

26:23.978 --> 26:28.762
With a full house of kings and aces.

26:36.703 --> 26:39.927
- A straight flush beats a house.
- Unbelievable.

26:40.453 --> 26:44.320
Hey, don't feel bad. Whenever there's
a winner, there's gotta be a loser.

26:44.420 --> 26:48.400
I found my wife in bed with a man
dressed in a Wombles suit

26:48.500 --> 26:52.928
while another man in a Barney outfit
stood above them taking a shit.

26:57.320 --> 26:59.653
Alright? Ready to go?

26:59.753 --> 27:02.353
I think so, yeah.

27:02.453 --> 27:05.195
It was really nice to meet all of you.

27:05.295 --> 27:08.362
- You too.
- Yeah, good luck.

27:08.462 --> 27:11.237
- Did you play?
- Yes.

27:11.337 --> 27:12.887
- Win?
- I don't know.

27:12.987 --> 27:15.534
- Cheerio.
- Bye now.

27:28.595 --> 27:31.278
So what did you think
when you saw me at the airport?

27:32.178 --> 27:34.497
I thought,
'She's really let herself go.'

27:35.728 --> 27:37.020
Speak for yourself.

27:37.120 --> 27:39.630
No, I guess I thought...

27:40.399 --> 27:44.170
that it was a shame
that we didn't keep in touch.

27:44.770 --> 27:47.154
Well, if you had stayed
and accepted my proposal?

27:48.128 --> 27:49.694
That was...

27:49.794 --> 27:53.464
a mad idea.

27:54.612 --> 27:57.220
I was just trying to get you
a Green Card.

27:57.320 --> 27:59.172
I know...

27:59.272 --> 28:01.495
but I still had another year in college.

28:01.595 --> 28:04.362
- The sensible decision.
- Yeah. Hard to argue against it.

28:05.495 --> 28:08.028
And then you got that super
awesome internship.

28:08.128 --> 28:10.084
Yeah.

28:10.678 --> 28:12.395
I always intended to come back.

28:14.762 --> 28:17.093
It's cool. It was just
a summer thing. Right?

28:17.193 --> 28:19.126
Right.

28:19.828 --> 28:24.762
Far be it from me to pull you away
from your simple thatch cottage

28:24.862 --> 28:26.995
- to the big city.
- Yeah.

28:27.095 --> 28:29.006
You probably didn't even
own shoes, did you?

28:29.106 --> 28:33.320
- Who can afford them?
- Just a bunch of freckles and a dream.

28:33.420 --> 28:35.595
- And my fighting skills.
- Yeah.

28:35.895 --> 28:38.877
How can you make a living without those?

28:41.003 --> 28:44.695
- It was... it was just an idea.
- Yeah.

28:45.195 --> 28:47.220
Chalk it up to a wild youth.

28:47.320 --> 28:50.002
Think of that tattoo
that you never ended up getting.

28:55.170 --> 28:57.295
- Here we go.
- The job?

28:57.395 --> 28:59.553
Hi, Vicky.

29:00.520 --> 29:03.681
Oh, it's kind of hard to hear you.
Hang on a second.

29:05.153 --> 29:09.266
Hey! Sorry. Yeah. Right.

29:12.237 --> 29:13.788
Okay.

29:24.012 --> 29:26.686
Not close enough?

29:27.553 --> 29:31.021
For someone who doesn't believe in lies,
you're really sticking your toe in.

29:31.121 --> 29:33.462
I know. Just be cool.

29:33.762 --> 29:35.417
Okay. Like you?

29:35.817 --> 29:39.603
The opposite of me.
If I was cool, I wouldn't be doing this.

29:39.703 --> 29:41.992
Where is she?

29:43.195 --> 29:45.154
She just got the job of her dreams.

29:46.053 --> 29:48.536
I love it when good things
happen to beautiful people.

29:49.712 --> 29:54.227
Well, thanks for the opportunity.

29:54.745 --> 29:57.284
Okay, bye.

30:01.053 --> 30:04.795
- Maybe I should tell her the truth.
- This will kick the ass.

30:04.895 --> 30:08.428
- So what if I don't have a girlfriend?
- I'm here. We're fucking doing this!

30:08.528 --> 30:09.978
- This is a bad idea.
- No.

30:10.078 --> 30:12.928
- Yeah. I'll just...
- No. No!

30:13.028 --> 30:16.317
You're a dirty liar now
just like the rest of us. Okay?

30:24.945 --> 30:27.939
I was thinking we should plan
a nice trip.

30:28.978 --> 30:31.900
I was thinking we should go away.

30:42.053 --> 30:44.373
The wine's not very bad.

30:44.473 --> 30:46.929
Two bottles, please.

30:51.862 --> 30:54.757
So you guys work together?
That's gotta be interesting.

30:55.970 --> 30:57.453
It has its moments.

30:57.553 --> 31:03.628
It is hard to control ourselves.
The relationship is very physical.

31:03.728 --> 31:05.500
Yeah.

31:07.653 --> 31:10.528
- How long was it before you...
- Became lovers?

31:10.728 --> 31:12.780
Sure.

31:13.653 --> 31:18.220
- It was, it was pretty soon, yeah.
- It was at a David Bowie concert.

31:18.320 --> 31:20.853
Well, not David Bowie,
but someone who look like him.

31:21.053 --> 31:25.226
What was their name? You know?
The name of the band that was not him?

31:26.778 --> 31:29.796
- Diamond Dogs.
- Yes, the Dogs.

31:29.896 --> 31:32.212
Well... We went just as friends.

31:32.312 --> 31:35.328
The David Bowie man,
he sings 'Life on Mars'

31:35.828 --> 31:41.445
and the crowd, it surge forward,
pressing our bodies together.

31:41.545 --> 31:48.137
And as David sing, we look
into each others' eyes as one.

31:48.237 --> 31:51.061
And then we kissed.

31:52.112 --> 31:54.596
Brilliant. It was a brilliant night.

32:05.478 --> 32:07.895
- You're very good at this.
- Just to make her jealous.

32:07.995 --> 32:10.712
Yeah, I got that when you compared me
to a fully inflamed stallion.

32:10.812 --> 32:13.503
It's Valentine's. The least I can do
is pretend we are fucking.

32:13.603 --> 32:16.382
By the time I am finished,
she will be dying to be with you.

32:16.482 --> 32:18.872
Look, it's not gonna happen.
She's got a boyfriend.

32:18.972 --> 32:21.503
The guy who Wendy left you for.
He must have done this, no?

32:21.603 --> 32:23.932
- Exactly.
- But it seemed to work for him.

32:26.278 --> 32:29.012
I'm not gonna be like the guy
who ran off with my fiancée.

32:30.112 --> 32:32.299
Maybe if you were,
you would not be here.

32:33.012 --> 32:36.575
- Who knows?
- This is obvious, Alan.

32:41.512 --> 32:45.397
Weren't you doing finance? I thought you
were going to be the next Gekko the Great.

32:45.497 --> 32:47.637
Just what the world needs.

32:47.737 --> 32:51.478
The bank is a pool of rats.
He told them to shove it up their asses.

32:51.578 --> 32:54.345
No, no, no, music is Alan's passion.

32:54.445 --> 32:56.053
You quit your job?

32:56.153 --> 32:58.506
Yeah, yeah.
I told them where to stick it.

32:59.612 --> 33:01.309
Aren't you full of surprises.

33:02.612 --> 33:05.053
- What is it you said?
- What?

33:05.153 --> 33:07.687
You know, after you leave?

33:08.278 --> 33:10.828
- Remind me again.
- That's it.

33:10.928 --> 33:16.474
He said to me, 'Beatrice, we must live
in the moment. Not in fucking suits.'

33:17.803 --> 33:22.412
That's cool. You know, I...
I had this consultant gig for a little while,

33:22.512 --> 33:26.094
and it was a pretty sweet deal,
but it just didn't do it for me. You know?

33:26.194 --> 33:28.623
Yeah, right, totally.

33:29.612 --> 33:32.850
And that's it, just like that,
never going back.

33:33.512 --> 33:35.680
I mean, why would you, right?

33:41.928 --> 33:46.172
If we had formed a band,
what would we have played?

33:46.272 --> 33:50.253
- I don't know. Johnny Cash?
- I love Hank Williams.

33:51.053 --> 33:52.095
Since when?

33:52.595 --> 33:55.253
Last couple of years. Why?
You don't think he'd be on my playlist?

33:55.353 --> 33:56.643
No, I'm happy he is,

33:56.743 --> 34:00.520
but I'm pretty sure I played you some
back in the day and you weren't that keen.

34:00.620 --> 34:02.778
I think I'd remember if you did.

34:03.478 --> 34:06.639
- Let's agree to disagree on that one.
- Just that one?

34:07.762 --> 34:12.213
Alan, could I speak to you
for just one second?

34:12.313 --> 34:15.822
It's alright. I was just about
to go to the restroom.

34:17.295 --> 34:19.543
- What's the problem?
- I've met someone.

34:20.570 --> 34:24.980
- You were in the bathroom for two minutes.
- I was coming out, he was going in.

34:25.080 --> 34:27.295
Our eyes, they meet.
Alan, I must leave with him now.

34:28.195 --> 34:30.007
In what universe do you think
this is appropriate...

34:30.108 --> 34:32.708
- I cannot help it!
- Billions of guys out there.

34:32.809 --> 34:36.462
Can't you just let one walk by
with his pants still on?

34:36.562 --> 34:39.322
Alan, this might be love.

34:42.295 --> 34:43.670
You don't want to spend
the rest of your life

34:43.770 --> 34:46.456
with someone you met
outside a toilet, do you?

34:48.152 --> 34:49.911
<i>Buena sera.</i>

34:50.112 --> 34:53.289
Well... well...

34:56.833 --> 34:58.699
- Go on.
- Have fun.

35:03.195 --> 35:05.036
Great.

35:09.537 --> 35:13.095
Hi. Beatrice had to help out a flatmate.

35:13.195 --> 35:15.453
They lost their key,
and they called Beatrice.

35:15.553 --> 35:19.553
She's really sorry she didn't get to say
goodbye. She's really, really sorry.

35:19.653 --> 35:21.703
Alan...

35:30.237 --> 35:32.660
I'm between girlfriends at the minute.

35:33.870 --> 35:35.389
So she...

35:36.200 --> 35:37.837
No.

35:37.937 --> 35:39.793
So...

35:41.537 --> 35:42.570
Why?

35:51.378 --> 35:54.767
Would you like to order
some coffee or dessert?

35:55.028 --> 35:58.039
I think we'll just take the check.

36:07.970 --> 36:12.787
Look, okay, I didn't quit my job.
I was fired.

36:12.887 --> 36:14.608
Any more lies you'd like to clear up?

36:16.028 --> 36:19.165
A couple of months before that,
I was stood up at the altar.

36:20.278 --> 36:22.537
- You were going to be married?
- Yeah.

36:22.637 --> 36:24.912
- You?
- Yeah.

36:25.612 --> 36:30.239
- To a real person?
- Yes, a real person. Wendy.

36:32.195 --> 36:34.012
Wendy.

36:34.112 --> 36:36.195
What?

36:36.295 --> 36:38.616
Nothing. I'm just surprised.

36:39.195 --> 36:42.153
- That I met someone else?
- Sure.

36:42.253 --> 36:45.084
Well, Wendy turned out to be
a lucky escape.

36:45.184 --> 36:47.370
I don't know what I was thinking.

36:47.470 --> 36:51.945
- Once bitten, though...
- It still doesn't explain the fake girlfriend.

36:56.028 --> 36:58.978
Look, okay, I promised you...

36:59.078 --> 37:02.737
that if you ever came here,
I'd give you a great night.

37:02.837 --> 37:07.029
I just wanna make good on that.
If you'll let me.

37:07.762 --> 37:12.512
- 100% honesty.
- Trust me, 100% is impossible.

37:12.612 --> 37:14.931
Well, as close to.

37:15.431 --> 37:19.956
You can ask me anything.
Like first gig, first crush.

37:20.056 --> 37:23.112
- Last time I whacked off.
- Sure.

37:23.212 --> 37:25.603
- What?
- That last one.

37:26.803 --> 37:28.652
Fine.

37:31.512 --> 37:33.607
Last week.

37:35.220 --> 37:39.253
I was on my own
in the apartment for once.

37:39.353 --> 37:43.453
There was a film on the telly.

37:43.553 --> 37:46.278
I had a couple of beers
and one thing led to another.

37:46.378 --> 37:48.217
I'm not proud of it, but there you go.

37:48.317 --> 37:50.115
Who was it?

37:51.112 --> 37:52.535
Helen Mirren.

37:55.153 --> 37:57.530
In 'The Queen'.

37:58.353 --> 38:00.483
You're a fan of the Royal Family?

38:00.583 --> 38:05.094
In the drunken scenario I came up with...
I was doing it for my country.

38:07.237 --> 38:10.809
- Is that enough truth for one night?
- I think we're just getting started.

38:15.012 --> 38:19.653
So you've just completely
taken yourself out of the game?

38:19.753 --> 38:23.428
You could say I'm keeping
the bench warm or something like that.

38:23.528 --> 38:26.137
Maybe you should think
about switching teams.

38:26.237 --> 38:30.714
- Probably wouldn't hurt.
- Maybe initially, but you'd get used to it.

38:32.237 --> 38:36.377
I guess I just haven't met anyone
who's ticked all the boxes.

38:37.378 --> 38:41.203
- I gave up ticking boxes a long time ago.
- Really?

38:41.303 --> 38:44.595
You just need to accept
that love is a lottery.

38:45.595 --> 38:49.100
Well, I don't like those odds.

38:50.253 --> 38:53.092
Well... tough shit.

39:02.012 --> 39:04.624
So is this all people do in Dublin?

39:05.820 --> 39:08.553
There's not that much to do
in the evenings.

39:08.653 --> 39:10.626
Maybe in the summertime...

39:11.226 --> 39:12.746
There must be something.

39:14.195 --> 39:16.947
Play a few games of pool.

39:18.153 --> 39:21.670
- Get a kebab?
- I thought you were a tourist advisor.

39:22.070 --> 39:25.999
We usually advise them
to go somewhere else.

39:26.903 --> 39:28.937
Okay.

39:29.237 --> 39:31.251
Let me think.

39:38.012 --> 39:41.031
<i>Do what you did yesterday</i>

39:41.331 --> 39:44.078
<i>Go on repeating</i>

39:44.178 --> 39:47.577
<i>'Cause my heart's only on fire</i>

39:47.677 --> 39:50.364
<i>When you are the teacher</i>

39:50.987 --> 39:53.694
<i>You take the torch and I</i>

39:54.194 --> 39:57.060
<i>Follow the leader.</i>

39:58.987 --> 40:02.016
<i>You'd be my master</i>

40:02.116 --> 40:04.440
<i>And I'll be your fever</i>

40:10.212 --> 40:15.904
<i>You told me your past
was taken by thieves</i>

40:16.304 --> 40:18.613
<i>Since then you've been running</i>

40:19.752 --> 40:21.973
<i>In search of reliefs</i>

40:22.570 --> 40:26.320
<i>You don't know when it's coming</i>

40:26.420 --> 40:29.333
<i>I don't know either</i>

40:42.803 --> 40:44.228
Nice.

40:45.312 --> 40:48.778
Dad worked here for a while.
We'd have lunch up here sometimes.

40:48.878 --> 40:51.970
If you don't mind me saying so,
he seems to have some...

40:52.070 --> 40:54.828
interesting views on women.

40:54.928 --> 40:58.220
Well, sometimes they don't turn out
the way you hoped, you know?

41:00.045 --> 41:01.518
Women or parents?

41:02.312 --> 41:05.703
Just parents.
They're not meant to be unpredictable.

41:05.803 --> 41:07.151
Okay.

41:13.253 --> 41:15.403
Your folks will be delighted
about the news.

41:18.237 --> 41:20.820
Well, unfortunately...

41:34.970 --> 41:37.449
High security.

41:46.462 --> 41:48.625
- Oh, crap!
- What?

41:54.612 --> 41:56.617
I'm sure someone will be up in a minute.

41:58.537 --> 42:00.870
Hello? Is there anyone there?

42:00.970 --> 42:04.912
Try calling the desk again.
We're on the roof of a hotel.

42:05.012 --> 42:07.545
Well, you know, someone has to hear us.

42:10.920 --> 42:14.175
Can't believe I'm gonna get
double pneumonia for this!

42:14.275 --> 42:16.765
You said the view was nice.

42:16.865 --> 42:21.528
I was being polite. I've already seen two...
three people throwing up down there!

42:22.028 --> 42:23.912
Okay.

42:24.012 --> 42:26.353
I can really see why
you wanted to stay here.

42:27.153 --> 42:32.835
Yeah, yeah. I was really hoping
to live it up here on the roof.

42:42.028 --> 42:45.762
If I still need to say sorry
about the whole Green Card thing...

42:45.862 --> 42:48.437
I think you're overestimating
your impact.

