01:06:56.045 --> 01:06:57.991
I mean,

01:06:58.091 --> 01:07:00.984
you're forty...
which has its own problems.

01:07:02.853 --> 01:07:05.517
I've been stood up at the altar.

01:07:06.945 --> 01:07:09.137
Epic fail.

01:07:09.670 --> 01:07:12.018
I was devastated,

01:07:12.918 --> 01:07:18.528
but that is so much better than trying
to break up 20 years later.

01:07:18.628 --> 01:07:22.703
And arguing over who owns
which Lonnie Donegan album.

01:07:22.803 --> 01:07:24.845
He's great.

01:07:26.087 --> 01:07:27.957
Yeah.

01:07:30.495 --> 01:07:32.594
I should've known Wendy wasn't a keeper.

01:07:38.445 --> 01:07:41.062
We picked the best time
to fuck this shit up is what I mean.

01:07:41.162 --> 01:07:42.387
Right.

01:07:50.170 --> 01:07:55.345
I guess a part of me always thought
that maybe you just met someone else,

01:07:55.445 --> 01:08:01.230
and the internship thing
was just a cover.

01:08:02.445 --> 01:08:04.944
I was just really scared.

01:08:07.528 --> 01:08:10.987
My family was here. My friends.

01:08:11.087 --> 01:08:14.712
My... career.

01:08:17.903 --> 01:08:20.925
Probably another year...

01:08:21.979 --> 01:08:27.639
before I even... thought of anyone else.

01:08:29.987 --> 01:08:32.363
Same here.

01:08:35.353 --> 01:08:36.895
Have you seen you?

01:08:40.545 --> 01:08:43.595
I'm not saying I haven't made up for it.

01:08:47.228 --> 01:08:50.515
We learn nothing from success.

01:08:52.002 --> 01:08:54.809
- To failure.
- Absolutely.

01:08:57.170 --> 01:09:00.903
- Is this tour of Dublin over?
- If you want.

01:09:01.002 --> 01:09:03.368
And if I don't?

01:09:04.127 --> 01:09:06.523
I know just the place.

01:10:04.170 --> 01:10:08.003
- Have you got enough?
- Yeah. Just about. You?

01:10:08.103 --> 01:10:10.424
Yeah, grand.

01:10:11.570 --> 01:10:14.295
Can't believe you've never heard
of one of these before.

01:10:14.395 --> 01:10:18.920
Yeah, well, we've had electricity
for a while. So...

01:10:21.987 --> 01:10:23.803
- Jesus!
- Is it too hot?

01:10:23.903 --> 01:10:25.687
Your feet are like ice!

01:10:26.944 --> 01:10:28.874
Sorry.

01:10:35.487 --> 01:10:37.213
Good night.

01:10:39.487 --> 01:10:41.846
Yeah, sleep tight.

01:10:47.128 --> 01:10:49.104
Why is it ribbed?

01:10:52.395 --> 01:10:54.736
It just is.

01:10:55.353 --> 01:10:57.812
My Granny's one was the same.

01:10:58.112 --> 01:11:01.577
It seems like a lot of trouble
for a bottle.

01:11:23.228 --> 01:11:24.808
Alan.

01:11:53.353 --> 01:11:56.828
Alice! Alice, what time's your flight?

01:11:56.928 --> 01:11:58.267
What time's your flight?

01:11:58.367 --> 01:12:01.345
- What?
- What time's your flight?

01:12:01.745 --> 01:12:03.028
Oh, fuck!

01:12:42.453 --> 01:12:46.553
Well, I guess we should be used
to saying goodbye at this stage.

01:12:46.653 --> 01:12:48.687
Yeah.

01:12:49.187 --> 01:12:52.253
- Let's stay in touch, though, this time.
- Definitely.

01:12:52.353 --> 01:12:54.645
- What's her name?
- Alice Rothmayer.

01:12:54.745 --> 01:12:56.282
- 'Roth' what?
- Rothmayer.

01:12:57.082 --> 01:12:59.303
Okay, I've got you a seat,
but you really need to go now.

01:12:59.403 --> 01:13:01.312
And no more funny business.

01:13:01.412 --> 01:13:03.642
Thanks.

01:13:19.187 --> 01:13:22.593
- Well, I guess this is it.
- Yeah.

01:13:24.087 --> 01:13:26.353
Take care of yourself.

01:13:26.453 --> 01:13:28.000
You too.

01:13:28.100 --> 01:13:30.420
You forgot your passport.
You have to go now.

01:13:30.520 --> 01:13:32.762
- I can bring you through.
- Okay, thanks.

01:13:32.862 --> 01:13:35.726
- Take the jacket.
- No, no, keep it. It's not even mine.

01:13:36.403 --> 01:13:39.612
- You really need to go now.
- Okay.

01:13:41.312 --> 01:13:43.322
Alice.

01:13:48.087 --> 01:13:50.120
Thanks for a great night.

01:13:51.720 --> 01:13:53.178
It's what I'm here for.

01:14:32.062 --> 01:14:36.417
You know, the first date I ever had
with your dad was such a disaster.

01:14:36.517 --> 01:14:39.303
All he could talk about was his dog.

01:14:39.987 --> 01:14:44.820
A couple of day later, he rings. I tell him,
'I don't think I can do another dog evening.'

01:14:44.920 --> 01:14:49.045
He asked me to give him another chance.
We met up a week later.

01:14:49.145 --> 01:14:52.737
Now, he'd spotted some books
I had in my bag before.

01:14:52.837 --> 01:14:57.287
So in that week, he'd gone out
and bought them and read them.

01:14:57.887 --> 01:15:00.528
I don't think we talked about dogs once.

01:15:00.628 --> 01:15:03.046
Well, maybe once.

01:15:12.287 --> 01:15:17.316
You can never tell how anything's
going to turn out. Nobody knows.

01:15:19.453 --> 01:15:21.610
But a good memory is worth something.

01:15:21.710 --> 01:15:24.406
Yeah. Yeah, I know.

01:15:38.553 --> 01:15:40.540
Oh, shit!

01:15:40.640 --> 01:15:43.473
I'm so proud of you, kiddo.

01:15:45.145 --> 01:15:47.350
Why? I only ever mess things up.

01:15:48.587 --> 01:15:51.412
You lose when you stop trying.

01:15:51.512 --> 01:15:52.945
Fuck it.

01:15:53.545 --> 01:15:57.678
- You go home and get some rest.
- No, it's alright. It's busy.

01:15:57.778 --> 01:16:00.070
That's an order.

01:16:14.945 --> 01:16:17.031
<i>Are you getting them?</i>

01:16:17.131 --> 01:16:19.005
<i>Yeah.</i>

01:16:19.862 --> 01:16:22.916
<i>It's a keeper, alright.</i>

01:16:28.812 --> 01:16:32.145
<i>Final call on Aer Lingus
flight EI105 to New York.</i>

01:16:32.245 --> 01:16:35.707
<i>This flight is now closing
through Gate 410.</i>

01:16:42.212 --> 01:16:44.795
Here's the great romancer.

01:16:44.895 --> 01:16:46.345
You guys not working today?

01:16:46.445 --> 01:16:49.537
Couldn't possibly face work
after that shite last night.

01:16:49.637 --> 01:16:52.045
Actually, there's still
some beers in the fridge.

01:16:52.145 --> 01:16:54.456
Bring us one of mine, would ya?

01:17:07.503 --> 01:17:10.254
Did Alice get off okay?

01:17:11.412 --> 01:17:13.232
Yeah.

01:17:14.778 --> 01:17:18.199
That's not one of mine.
You know the beer I like.

01:17:18.820 --> 01:17:21.937
- Jeez, would you look at yourself?
- What?

01:17:22.037 --> 01:17:24.562
Look, not all women out there are trying
to screw you over every time, okay?

01:17:24.662 --> 01:17:26.637
Some of them, maybe,
but there are lots of nice ones.

01:17:27.037 --> 01:17:28.903
Once bitten, twice shy.

01:17:29.003 --> 01:17:30.928
Joe, your wife left ya
because you're the kind of guy

01:17:31.028 --> 01:17:33.715
that can fart his favourite TV theme tune,
and somewhere along the line,

01:17:33.815 --> 01:17:36.503
that wasn't good enough for her.
Now, I'm sorry, but it's true.

01:17:37.103 --> 01:17:41.286
Look, it's all painful, but if you're not in,
you can't win. You gotta take a chance.

01:17:41.962 --> 01:17:44.404
You can't just give up.

01:17:49.003 --> 01:17:50.885
A bit harsh.

01:17:56.453 --> 01:17:59.587
- What are you doin'?
- What does it look like I'm doin'?

01:17:59.687 --> 01:18:03.088
- Alan, this is crazy.
- Yeah, I know.

01:18:03.188 --> 01:18:06.887
- What if she's a looper?
- Then I'll have a story to tell.

01:18:06.987 --> 01:18:09.755
It's a long way to go.

01:18:10.287 --> 01:18:12.624
I'll let you know how it got on.

01:18:12.724 --> 01:18:14.570
Sorry, Joe, again.

01:18:14.670 --> 01:18:16.803
It was the theme tune from 'Frasier'.

01:18:16.903 --> 01:18:19.397
It's not easy to fart
'tossed salad and scrambled eggs'.

01:18:19.497 --> 01:18:21.637
- Here, take some money.
- Dad, you've given me enough.

01:18:21.737 --> 01:18:24.770
Think of it as relationship insurance.

01:18:24.870 --> 01:18:27.574
There's always a room for you here.

01:18:30.470 --> 01:18:32.105
I hope it works out for ya.

01:19:34.312 --> 01:19:37.129
I have to go back.

01:19:39.512 --> 01:19:41.966
I don't have to stay here.

